{
  "texts": [
    "The EvalMod step of the bootstrapping takes as input the message I(Y) • Q + ∆m(Y) with Y = X N/2M (M being the number of complex slots) and aims to vanish the integer polynomial I(Y) by homomorphically evaluating the function f mod = x mod 1 in the union of intervals ∪ K i=-K [i -ϵ, i + ϵ], with [-ϵ, ϵ] being the expected interval where the original message lies.",
    "The coefficients of the polynomial I(Y) are the sum of h + 1 uniform random variables in [-0.5, 0.5), with h the Hamming weight of the secret.",
    "There have been many works proposing different approaches for the EvalMod step.",
    "However, all practical approaches follow the same blueprint, which is to find a good polynomial approximation of f mod.",
    "Which function is chosen to closely match f mod and how the polynomial approximation is done has no effect on the failure probability."
  ]
}